Package it.polimi.ingsw.model.player

Class ScoreList

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.ingsw.model.player.ScoreList
  • public abstract class ScoreList
extends java.lang.Object
    This class determines the amount of points a Player hands out to his opponents from whom they took Damage.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      private static int FRENETIC_OFFSET
      The amount of deaths it would take to a regular Player to score the same number of points to each opponent as the number of points awarded by who died for the first time, but on final frenzy.
      private static int VALUE_0
      The amount of points that a kill is worth such that the sum of the amount of times the Player had already died in the past and the number of Players who dealt either more Damage or the same amount of Damage, the first of which being earlier, on the same kill on the same Player is equal to 0.
      private static int VALUE_1
      The amount of points that a kill is worth such that the sum of the amount of times the Player had already died in the past and the number of Players who dealt either more Damage or the same amount of Damage, the first of which being earlier, on the same kill on the same Player is equal to 1.
      private static int VALUE_2
      The amount of points that a kill is worth such that the sum of the amount of times the Player had already died in the past and the number of Players who dealt either more Damage or the same amount of Damage, the first of which being earlier, on the same kill on the same Player is equal to 2.
      private static int VALUE_3
      The amount of points that a kill is worth such that the sum of the amount of times the Player had already died in the past and the number of Players who dealt either more Damage or the same amount of Damage, the first of which being earlier, on the same kill on the same Player is equal to 3.
      private static int VALUE_INFINITY
      The amount of points that a kill is worth such that the sum of the amount of times the Player had already died in the past and the number of Players who dealt either more Damage or the same amount of Damage, the first of which being earlier, on the same kill on the same Player is equal to or greater than 4.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static int get​(int index,
                      boolean frenetic)
        Returns the appropriate amount of points based on the conditions described by the arguments.
        Parameters:
        index - the sum of the index of the opponent in the list of opponents who damaged a Player, and the number of times said Player had died in the past.
        frenetic - whether or not the Player is on final frenzy. Final frenzy kills are worth as many points as a regular kill on a Player killed three (FRENETIC_OFFSET) additional times, therefore many fewer points.
        Returns:
        the amount of points to give to the opponent who damaged the considered Player.
